Mexico Stocks: Banorte, Cemex, Soriana, Grupo Mexico Advance

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-12-09T16:17:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-09/mexico-stocks-banorte-cemex-soriana-grupo-mexico-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:51 a.m. local time.  The IPC index rose 1 percent to 36,999.09.  Mexican stocks followed global equities higher after
European leaders agreed to boost a rescue fund and tighten
budget rules to stem the region’s debt crisis.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO)  , the largest cement maker in the
Americas, climbed 3.4 percent to 6.76 pesos. Lender  Grupo
Financiero Banorte SAB (GFNORTEO)   rose 2.8 percent to 45.50
pesos.  Organizacion Soriana SAB (SORIANAB)  , Mexico’s second-
largest grocery store chain, added 2.3 percent to 32.97 pesos.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , the country’s largest
mining company, increased 1.3 percent to 37.93 pesos. Copper
futures for March delivery rose as much as 1.9 percent in  New
York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
